      <section class="readme-section" id="prompt-library">
        <h2>Automation prompt library</h2>
        <p>Drop these prompts into Codex, Claude, or Cursor to drive the SweetLink CLI without typing everything yourself.</p>
        <div class="prompt-grid">
          <article class="prompt-card">
            <header>
              <h3>End-to-end smoke prompt</h3>
            </header>
            <pre id="prompt-smoke">You are operating the SweetLink CLI on my machine.
Goals:
1. Ensure the SweetLink daemon is running locally.
2. Launch the SweetLink browser demo on http://localhost:4000.
3. Open a controlled Chrome window pointed at the demo and wait for the handshake to complete.
4. Capture a screenshot of the "Screenshot Target" card.

Checklist (run sequentially):
- pnpm sweetlink:daemon
- pnpm --filter @sweetlink/example-basic-web dev
- pnpm sweetlink open --controlled --env dev --url http://localhost:4000 --timeout 45
- pnpm sweetlink sessions
- pnpm sweetlink screenshot &lt;sessionId&gt; --selector "#screenshot-card"

Report back with the screenshot path and any console errors logged by SweetLink.</pre>
            <div class="copy-row">
              <button
                type="button"
                class="copy-btn copy-icon-btn"
                data-copy-source="prompt-smoke"
                data-copy-label="Smoke prompt"
                data-copy-icon="ðŸ“‹"
                data-copy-success-icon="âœ“"
                aria-label="Copy smoke prompt"
              >
                <span aria-hidden="true">ðŸ“‹</span>
              </button>
            </div>
          </article>
          <article class="prompt-card">
            <header>
              <h3>DevTools triage prompt</h3>
            </header>
            <pre id="prompt-devtools">You have access to the SweetLink CLI and the chrome-devtools MCP.
Investigate runtime issues in the SweetLink browser demo and summarize findings.

Steps to run:
- pnpm sweetlink sessions
- pnpm sweetlink devtools console --tail 50
- pnpm mcp:call chrome-devtools.take_snapshot
- pnpm mcp:call chrome-devtools.list_console_messages

If the console contains errors, capture the failing selectors and propose fixes. Otherwise, confirm the demo is healthy.</pre>
            <div class="copy-row">
              <button
                type="button"
                class="copy-btn copy-icon-btn"
                data-copy-source="prompt-devtools"
                data-copy-label="DevTools prompt"
